'''沙烏地阿拉伯皇家战略火箭军'''  ( {{lang-ar|قوة الصواريخ الإستراتيجيه الملكية السعودية}}，{{lang-en|Royal Saudi Strategic Missile Force}}） 是沙烏地阿拉伯皇家武装力量的五大分支之一 ，成立于1987年 ，缩写是RSSMF。现任指挥官是加热拉·欧拉维特（{{lang-ar|جار الله العلويط،}}）少将。

==主要武器==
RSSMF主要武器是中国出售给沙特的[[东风-3远程弹道导弹|东风-3远程弹道导弹]]。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://news.ifeng.com/mil/2/detail_2012_07/08/15864193_0.shtml |title=以色列媒体称中国或向沙特出口东风-21并建设基地 |accessdate=2014-05-01 |archive-date=2014-01-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140106040522/http://news.ifeng.com/mil/2/detail_2012_07/08/15864193_0.shtml |dead-url=no }}</ref>1987年为[[金轮工程|出口沙特阿拉伯]]的开发变体东风3A中程弹道导弹，它具有射程可达2800公里的常规高爆弹头（2150千克）。<ref>SinoDefence [http://www.sinodefence.com/strategic/missile/df3.asp "DongFeng 3 (CSS-2) Intermediate-Range Ballistic Missile"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130814034822/http://www.sinodefence.com/strategic/missile/df3.asp |date=2013-08-14 }}, ''[[sinodefence|sinodefence]]'', 27 February 2009.</ref> 根据报道，1988年中国出售了30-120枚弹道导弹和 9-12辆发射载具，虽然没有沙特试射这些弹道导弹的报道。有些消息来源称沙特有意向购买中国的[[東風-15短程彈道飛彈|東風-15短程彈道飛彈]]與[[東風-21中程彈道飛彈|東風-21中程彈道飛彈]]。<ref>Jefrey Lewis - Arms Control Wonk.  [http://lewis.armscontrolwonk.com/archive/6688/saudi-arabias-strategic-dyad "Saudi Arabia’s Strategic Dyad"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151006001838/http://lewis.armscontrolwonk.com/archive/6688/saudi-arabias-strategic-dyad |date=2015-10-06 }} ''Arms Control Wonk'' , 15 July 2013.</ref>

==导弹基地==
两个比较老的基地是：位于利雅得市西南450千米的[[苏莱伊迈|苏莱伊迈]]导弹基地（{{lang-en|Al Sulayyil ballistic missile base}}）和利雅得以南90千米处的贾法里导弹基地（Al Jufayr ballistic missile base）。

2008年建成了新的瓦塔哈导弹基地（Al-Watah ballistic missile base），距离利雅得市200千米。

==公开信息==
RSSMF的预算和人员数量编制是绝密的。在2009年沙特和海湾国家宣布希望获得核武器制衡伊朗核计划之后，RSSMF的战略作用更加重要。沙特国王阿卜杜拉和沙特前情报首脑和沙特驻美国大使[[图尔基·本·费萨尔·阿勒沙特|图尔基·本·费萨尔·阿勒沙特]]亲王提到了这个。<ref>US embassy cables: Saudi official warns Gulf states may go nuclear [http://www.theguardian.com/world/us-embassy-cables-documents/189229] {{Wayback|url=http://www.theguardian.com/world/us-embassy-cables-documents/189229 |date=20170810130507 }}, ''The Guardian'', 28 November 2010.</ref> 
<ref>Saudi Arabia urges US attack on Iran to stop nuclear programme [http://www.theguardian.com/world/2010/nov/28/us-embassy-cables-saudis-iran] {{Wayback|url=http://www.theguardian.com/world/2010/nov/28/us-embassy-cables-saudis-iran |date=20171109000914 }} ''The Guardian'', 28 November 2010.</ref>
<ref>Riyadh will build nuclear weapons if Iran gets them, Saudi prince warns [http://www.theguardian.com/world/2011/jun/29/saudi-build-nuclear-weapons-iran] {{Wayback|url=http://www.theguardian.com/world/2011/jun/29/saudi-build-nuclear-weapons-iran |date=20171206072226 }} ''The Guardian'', 29 June 2011.</ref> 
<ref>Dennis Ross: Saudi king vowed to obtain nuclear bomb after Iran [http://www.haaretz.com/news/diplomacy-defense/dennis-ross-saudi-king-vowed-to-obtain-nuclear-bomb-after-iran-1.433294] {{Wayback|url=http://www.haaretz.com/news/diplomacy-defense/dennis-ross-saudi-king-vowed-to-obtain-nuclear-bomb-after-iran-1.433294 |date=20150911095622 }} ''Haaretz'', 30 May 2012.</ref>
<ref>King Says Saudi Arabia Would Need Nukes to Counter Iran Arsenal [http://www.nti.org/gsn/article/saudi-arabia-would-need-nukes-counter-iran-arsenal-king/] {{Wayback|url=http://www.nti.org/gsn/article/saudi-arabia-would-need-nukes-counter-iran-arsenal-king/ |date=20171206072235 }} ''The Nuclear Threat Initiative'', 30 May 2012.</ref>
有些专家推测，考虑到沙特给巴基斯坦的核武器计划提供了资金，沙特可能通过巴基斯坦获得了核武器。来自BBC的一份报告指出：第一种可能是 2003年沙特通过现金交易获取了核弹头; 第二种可能是巴基斯坦核力量部署在沙特阿拉伯境内"。<ref>Mark Urban: Saudi nuclear weapons 'on order' from Pakistan [http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-middle-east-24823846] {{Wayback|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-middle-east-24823846 |date=20180301194451 }} ''BBC News'', 6 November 2013.</ref>

